The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Wednesday, April 30, 2003 				 Case against truant doctor 
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Ranaghat (Nadia), April 29: The sub-divisional judicial magistrate here today asked police to start a suo-motu case against a doctor for alleged negligence due to which a youth had died while under his treatment.																								On April 1, Prahlad Sarkar of Joygopalpur in Ranaghat was admitted to the sub-divisional hospital after he was injured in a football match. The father, Atul Sarkar, said his condition started deteriorating from the third day.																								When Prahlads condition worsened, my elder son went to Rahaman Alam, the doctor. But he could not be located. A hospital staff said he was in a private dispensary. Magistrate Yasmin Fatma asked the police to treat Atuls complaint as an FIR.
